  "topic": "Restaking over time",
  "summary": "Restaking lets staked ETH (and other assets) be re-pledged to secure additional services, pioneered by EigenLayer (mainnet 2023, deposits opened broadly in 2024). The narrative exploded in 2024: EigenLayer TVL rose from ~$1.3B at end-2023 to a ~$20.1B peak on 2024-06-06, while liquid restaking tokens (LRTs) — ether.fi, Renzo, Kelp, Puffer, Swell — layered on top, with ether.fi peaking above $10B in Dec 2024. Competitors Symbiotic and Karak launched in mid/late-2024. After the points-farming and airdrop incentives wound down, the sector partially normalized in 2025: EigenLayer rebounded to a fresh ~$22.1B ATH on 2025-08-14 (helped by ETH price), then declined to ~$12.6B by end-2025 and ~$5.0B by mid-June 2026 as restaked ETH outflowed and slashing went live (Apr 2025). LRTs followed: ether.fi held ~$8B through 2025 but fell to ~$3.0B by mid-2026; Renzo and Karak collapsed >90% from peaks. All figures are USD TVL from the DefiLlama API as of 2026-06-16. Note: LRTs deposit INTO EigenLayer, so summing 'Restaking' + 'Liquid Restaking' categories double-counts overlapping ETH; the combined-market series is gross summed TVL and overstates net unique value locked.",
